<h1><font color="#5C8526">Milestone : Minimal Cover</font></h1>
<ul><li><h2>A set of functional dependencies F is minimal if it satisfies the following conditions :</h2></li>
<li><h2>1.  Every dependency in F has a single attribute for its right hand side</h2></li>
<li><h2>2.  We cannot replace any dependence X --&gt; A in F with a dependency Y --&gt; A, where Y is  a proper subset of X and still have a set of dependencies that is equivalent to F.</h2></li>
<li><h2>3.  We cannot remove any dependency from F and still have a set of dependencies that is equivalent to F.</h2></li>
<li><h2>A minimal cover of a set of functional dependencies F is a minimal set of dependencies Fmin that is equivalent to F.</h2></li>
</ul></body>
